The food at Hash, the restaurant just off of the lobby, was fabulous for breakfast.	We didn't feel comfortable venturing out at night, but the Erwin has a great alternative - the roof top bar 'High'.	There's a rooftop bar on the seventh floor that is worth a visit (especially around sundown) and a restaurant on the first floor (Hash) where guests get 25% off -- good food and very fair prices.	They have a roof-top bar and seating area, and a bar and small dining area next to the lobby.